LanguageName: Wichí Lhamtés Güisnay (Misón La Paz dialect)

MetadataComments: Assigned Iron Ossetian based on Glottolog
Data from Erich Round, ask Eric by mail
Unlike the SPA doculect with the same phonemes, this one lists the source language (Standard French).
The borrowing language (Bajjika) was previously considered a dialect of Maithili and has no glottocode or ISO code of its own.
The grammar states that this consonant appears in loan words from Persian and Arabic, but not only those two languages.
the status of /z/ might have been affected by the introduction of loan words into the Koyaga language.

Taylor uses non-standard phonological orthography and compares the language to English. This might need to be checked.  

Stennes, page 14 (bottom) there's a note on borrowing consonant clusters.

Should we consider this grammar as two different doculects? Glottolog doesn't do so, but for our project it would be definatelly clearer, because sometimes the same sound is borrowed in one dialect but not in the other or sometimes it is a new phoneme in one dialect but a distrubutional change in the other.
